<br>
Halflings and Hell by Dragoon<br>
       </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Keep a medium sized party, 4 to 5 members at a time. Merry will keep Boromir alive with his exertion ability to add his power to a companion&#39;s. He should be able to stay alive until you can get a Gandalf or an Aragorn in play. Pippen and Sam serve as cannon fodder to block large minions and take archery damage. There should be enough events in the game that you should be able to keep at least one hobbit alive along with Frodo. Make sure to play the &quot;hobbit healing circle,&quot; Farmer Maggot and Hobbit Party Guest, as early as possible. The Gaffer is almost automatically put in play thanks to Bag End. A Talent For Not Being Seen is invaluable at all times. Remeber to power up Merry BEFORE you lend his strength to an ally.<br>
<br>
The Shadow is pretty straightforward. Hit your opponent early and often with the lower costing Uruks and use the breeding pits towards site 6 or 7 depending on how fast you burn through the deck. <br>
<br>
Weaknesses:<br>
   Site [7] Anduin Confluence is deadly to the &quot;hobbit healing cirlce.&quot;<br>
   More minions than companions, be ready to sacrifice your men first.<br>
<br>
Have Fun </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
